    nvl clear


translate English day10_cr_4870da84:


    "\n When I come to, I'm lying in bed. I fell asleep without the blanket on. I can still see a faint bruise on my knee."


translate English day10_cr_25bd7323:


    et "That proves that I was worshiping someone all night."


translate English day10_cr_bad53b57:



    nvl clear
    "\n As memories of yesterday come drifting back, I feel a tired headache.{w} My eyes are so dry I can barely blink. Worried, I reach up to my mouth and come back with the remnants of dried drool.{w} Apparently I've overslept."


translate English day10_cr_1f566f41:


    "Despite knowing that, I don't get out of bed.{w} I don't hurry to throw on clothes and rush down the hallway. A yawn escapes me instead of a breath, lamenting my position.{w} Yesterday--those moments I spent holding Claire's hand, all day, made me realize how I'd broken the rules I'd set for myself."


translate English day10_cr_6fe68a0c:


    et "All at once, they'd come crumbling down into a miserable pile, as if mocking all that time and effort I put in."


translate English day10_cr_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day10_cr_9f6a6d39:


    "\n It's as quiet outside the room now as it was in the middle of the night.{w} I open the old door and peer out into the silence, but as the door creaks open, I hear something else.{w} There's a paper hanging from a thumbtack on the frame."


translate English day10_cr_cb17fc72:


    "The handwriting on the brown paper is neat and tidy, just like its owner.{w} It hasn't run, either--the ink must have been expensive.{w} That's all I need to know who wrote this note."


translate English day10_cr_6eac0e15:


    "\"We will be waiting for you at the temple.\"{w} ...But, of course, I don't plan on going to the temple today."


translate English day10_cr_523c49bb:


    et "But when I think about her sitting alone in that musty, dismal place, my only choice is to go and see her."


translate English day10_cr_53974ec7:


    nar "I find Claire in the stairwell, as always."


translate English day10_cr_e6582e00:


    nar "She turns from her gaze out the window, then gives me a baleful look."


translate English day10_cr_0539ebe8:


    nar "I too easily respond with a smile."


translate English day10_cr_5b6d1ce9:


    cr "I was just thinking you wouldn't come, and I was about to go home."


translate English day10_cr_07d79f63:


    pl "Sorry, sorry. How long have you been here?"


translate English day10_cr_b4346470:


    cr "Hmm... An hour?{w} Or maybe two... I got to the temple early this morning."


translate English day10_cr_6520f966:


    pl "Two hours? You were waiting that long...?{w} What would you have done if I hadn't come?"


translate English day10_cr_d03a7d67:


    cr "I could always go spend time with others.{w} I planned to be at the temple all day anyway, so..."


translate English day10_cr_68761839:


    cr "But enough about me! Did you just wake up, Lord [na]?{w} The sun's already at its highest point!"


translate English day10_cr_a90e321b:


    pl "Nobody came to wake me up, so I thought it was a holiday. And isn't the sun always right up there in the middle of the sky?"


translate English day10_cr_9724739f:


    cr "Why, that's so impudent of you.{w} But I'm glad to see you got back safe yesterday."


translate English day10_cr_2e8d91be:


    cr "You seemed very out of sorts when you left. I was worried."


translate English day10_cr_65a2ea71:


    pl "I managed.{w} As for you..."


translate English day10_cr_caf61963:


    nar "I study Claire as she comes down to meet me, feeling ueasy."


translate English day10_cr_fadb3325:


    nar "Each time she sees me looking at her, she always shows me a wound, like a bruise or a hand mark."


translate English day10_cr_38324ba2:


    nar "She seems to want me to see her bruises again today."


translate English day10_cr_a32a96c5:


    pl "...No earring? I remember giving you one yesterday."


translate English day10_cr_47dadb24:


    nar "That must be the right answer, because she sadly touches her ear."


translate English day10_cr_a3291881:


    nar "Her little earlobe is still swelled, the red droplets of blood having hardened around it."


translate English day10_cr_1e7961cb:


    cr "It was a gift from you, and I wanted to treasure it. But..."


translate English day10_cr_231c3aa9:


    cr "I don't think he likes me getting accessories like that, or presents.{w} I knew he'd be angry with me for getting home so late..."


translate English day10_cr_72ed6efd:


    cr "But I never imagined... that he'd rip it out my ear."


translate English day10_cr_49a69a7e:


    cr "I don't know how to face you now, Lord [na]."


translate English day10_cr_52dd8d97:


    pl "Hey, you didn't think that would happen either, right?{w} I should be the one apologizing. I shouldn't have done it. I'm sorry."


translate English day10_cr_ceb34530:


    cr "Mm... Now that I don't have the earring...{w} If it stays like this forever, won't the hole close up?"


translate English day10_cr_b690c6a0:


    pl "Well... Even if it does, piercings are forbidden at the temple, right?{w} I might as well take mine out. Gotta maintain appearances, and all that."


translate English day10_cr_801ae8cb:


    cr "What? That may be true, but I believe they're one of your most charming aspects."


translate English day10_cr_b2d57e4e:


    cr "Instead, we should go have fun in town together again.{w} I'll pick something out for you that'll look great."


translate English day10_cr_c5134b2c:


    nar "I can't believe she'd casually bring up yesterday like that."


translate English day10_cr_e061eeef:


    nar "I definitely asked her to pretend like it never happened. Did she forget already?"


translate English day10_cr_ff85a69f:


    nar "No, this is Claire I'm talking to. Maybe she's angry I asked her to do that."


translate English day10_cr_d4d1cf50:


    pl "But that's not the important thing right now, is it?{w} Are you just going to let him beat you forever? We have to think of another way to resolve it something."


translate English day10_cr_fb1bf0a6:


    cr "To resolve what?"


translate English day10_cr_d9235364:


    pl "...My viewpoints aside, how do YOU feel?"


translate English day10_cr_8a461696:


    cr "Me?{w} Are you telling me to think for myself?"


translate English day10_cr_951a39d3:


    cr "Lord [na], you tend to have an optimistic view, and tend not to treat anything with very much import."


translate English day10_cr_e9a7f1db:


    pl "Hey, I think about a lot of stuff too, you know.{w} But I can't come up with the answer to this one, so I'm asking you."


translate English day10_cr_111b3291:


    pl "I think you're being the carefree one here--despite everything, you still can't think of a solution."


translate English day10_cr_924a544e:


    cr "There isn't one, and that's why I don't think about it...{w} You didn't have to go that far."


translate English day10_cr_f215d5bc:


    pl "Er, I'm... sorry.{w} I'm doing my best to think of something. But like you say, there's no answer in sight."


translate English day10_cr_f45b8e2d:


    pl "I just wanted to complain about not being able to do anything when you're suffering like this."


translate English day10_cr_6dc44681:


    cr "......"


translate English day10_cr_6cdddfa7:


    pl "How did things go with your parents after that?{w} You said it was kinda awkward."


translate English day10_cr_195dd646:


    cr "I don't know.{w} I usually contact them every night before going to sleep, but I got back so late that I couldn't do so."


translate English day10_cr_94c83991:


    cr "They called me, too, but I was too scared to pick up..."


translate English day10_cr_1e457853:


    cr "I'm sure they're worried. Oh, what should I do...?"


translate English day10_cr_0627aedd:


    pl "Why not be honest with and reveal what's going on?{w} You're marrying that guy, aren't you?"


translate English day10_cr_15c476f4:


    cr "......"


translate English day10_cr_1ce45ad0:


    pl "...Claire?"


translate English day10_cr_45f012b2:


    cr "Yes, that's what I should do..."


translate English day10_cr_5c3ddd37:


    cr "How about you go meet my parents, Lord [na], and we tell them what's happening?{w} And we can even have my fiancé there."


translate English day10_cr_ce5e2020:


    pl "M-Me?{w} What about you?!"


translate English day10_cr_7956921b:


    cr "Once everything is set up, I'll come out.{w} I'll explain in advance that there's someone else I want to marry now, but..."


translate English day10_cr_f3e5d673:


    cr "If I explain why I want to call off the engagement, they're sure to be terribly shocked."


translate English day10_cr_c5d03771:


    cr "I don't know if I'll be able to watch that."


translate English day10_cr_f2424fd6:


    pl "No, well, that's fine and all, but why haven't you told your parents about any of this before now?"


translate English day10_cr_48a83c77:


    pl "Don't you talk to them every day?"


translate English day10_cr_18c6aaed:


    cr "In my opinion, they only want the best, happiest life for me, and they went with the best choice to that end."


translate English day10_cr_cf417e2a:


    cr "I don't want to make them sad."


translate English day10_cr_865af509:


    nar "But it's okay for me to be the one doing the difficult part?{w} I can sense Claire's gloomy voice brightening back up."


translate English day10_cr_10bce805:


    nar "Her expressions of sadness and loneliness seem somehow exaggerated, like she's actually enjoying this situation."


translate English day10_cr_8ffe2256:


    nar "I'm kind of used to it by now."


translate English day10_cr_eff72c3d:


    nar "That frilled skirt spread over the cold staircase--the midnight sunlight shining in to light up the dark room."


translate English day10_cr_5f5ab67b:


    nar "Until now, she's been the heroine of her own tragic love story.{w} And now she's finally moving to the ending of it."


translate English day10_cr_1146f52c:


    pl "Is that why you come to see me?"


translate English day10_cr_c05d09a6:


    cr "Huh?"


translate English day10_cr_44c5fe44:


    pl "...Let me think about it.{w} I've gotta get myself mentally prepared anyway."


translate English day10_cr_ab61c85a:


    cr "Oh, yes, of course.{w} I just knew you'd agree."


translate English day10_cr_045a4d54:


    cr "But we don't have much time left at this point.{w} Next month... next week. No more."


translate English day10_cr_b82dfd0c:


    cr "That's when the wedding ceremony will take place. You understand, right?"


translate English day10_cr_eee5febb:


    pl "Yeah... Right, you mentioned that. Feels like so long ago now."


translate English day10_cr_8f1ff2d5:


    cr "Time still passes when lost in thought, Lord [na].{w} How are you feeling today?"


translate English day10_cr_14b47fe9:


    cr "You're late anyway. Would you like to go out again?"


translate English day10_cr_49ff289c:


    pl "No, it's fine!{w} For today, well... I didn't work yesterday, so I really, really have to today. I think lunch is soon, too."


translate English day10_cr_891fca56:


    pl "You're hungry, right? Why don't you go to the cafeteria?"


translate English day10_cr_620b62ad:


    cr "Hmm... Now that you mention it, I haven't eaten since yesterday.{w} And neither have you, if I'm not mistaken."


translate English day10_cr_922eed89:


    pl "I'm fine, really... I'll figure something about for myself. You go over there."


translate English day10_cr_cbecfb4c:


    cr "...Do you not want to be with me?{w} I'm trying to be considerate of your feelings..."


translate English day10_cr_b60c224a:


    cr "So why have you been acting like this?"


translate English day10_cr_9569d863:


    pl "That's not what I mean... I'm just not hungry.{w} I was just sleeping until moments ago, remember?"


translate English day10_cr_71c506bc:


    cr "Would you have said no if it were Maya asking you and not me?"


translate English day10_cr_01fd5de4:


    pl "What does she have to do with anything?"


translate English day10_cr_ac16803a:


    cr "Would you have, though?{w} I just want you to think about my position a little more."


translate English day10_cr_49e1b661:


    pl "You're the one acting weird!{w} Do you have any idea how much I've been--" with sshake


translate English day10_cr_1554f731:


    cr "Eek...!" with sshake


translate English day10_cr_3d234c2b:


    pl "Wh-What? You, uh...{w} What...{w} What did you just, I..."


translate English day10_cr_15c476f4_1:


    cr "......"


translate English day10_cr_46018ce1:


    pl "...I'm sorry. I was ignoring your feelings again.{w} I really didn't mean to."


translate English day10_cr_919c9e26:


    pl "And I'm really just not hungry right now.{w} This is all my fault."


translate English day10_cr_14d8d8e1:


    pl "You're really important to me, and I love you more than anyone in the world. So please, cheer up."


translate English day10_cr_620b4ec8:


    cr "...I'm not angry with you, but if you insist, then I'll go have something to eat."


translate English day10_cr_20a7acc9:


    cr "As I said, I plan on being at the temple all day.{w} You can come see me at any time."


translate English day10_cr_c6bd12dc:


    pl "Right... I'll see you later, then."


translate English day10_cr_be5f7298:


    nar "I leave as if I'm escaping from her.{w} Honestly, I wasn't planning on working."


translate English day10_cr_e34c5246:


    nar "I have fun when I'm with her.{w} She's clever, and great at talking, and we have amazing conversations. There's never a dull moment."


translate English day10_cr_e58306af:


    nar "But why does she have to talk about all that with me?{w} How can she expect me to be satisfied by just listening?"


translate English day10_cr_6ef2978d:


    nar "The last time I enjoyed one of our conversations, we lived in different worlds."


translate English day10_cr_12aa07d0:


    nar "Even if it was built on missing information, we could understand each other.{w} But now we're in the same situation."


translate English day10_cr_f54807c5:


    nar "We have the same problem now, and our own mindsets, values, and reactions are turning out to be completely different.{w} It's disappointing."


translate English day10_cr_3057ef36:


    nar "Because I've realized we CAN'T understand each other."


translate English day10_cr_de7e81c5:


    nar "I've been doing nothing but think about her lately.{w} It's wearing me down."


translate English day10_cr_518d019f:


    nar "Every time Claire blames herself or humiliates someone else, I want to kill her.{w} I want to kill all the people causing her pain."


translate English day10_cr_53b9f493:


    nar "I either love her more than anything, or hate her more than anything--and it almost seems like the same thing."


translate English day10_cr_ecbaadb7:


    ex1 "[na]? Is that you?"


translate English day10_cr_0353f6d7:


    nar "An unfamiliar voice calls out to me while I'm walking down the central hallway.{w} I look up and see a girl I don't know."


translate English day10_cr_6d50a25b:


    pl "Huh?"


translate English day10_cr_fd173adb:


    ex1 "You didn't come today, so I figured you were sick. But you look alright!"


translate English day10_cr_6aa93d53:


    nar "Before I can answer, she pats me on the shoulder and walks past."


translate English day10_cr_0be1743e:


    nar "I know her...{w} She's the priest from the disposal team who was talking to Claire yesterday morning, during all that ruckus.{w} What's going on?"


translate English day10_cr_8ccf4f47:


    nar "I didn't go back to my room after grabbing Claire's hand and leaving the temple.{w} Is that why?"


translate English day10_cr_81001ef1:


    nar "What has the disposal team been talking about while I've been gone?"


translate English day10_cr_eedb4cfc:


    nar "I know nobody will be there, but I head for my room anyway."


translate English day10_cr_d34a0781:


    nar "As I walk down the passage, I feel a dampness in the air, just like the first day I was here.{w} A kind of dank heaviness, though not with an odor."


translate English day10_cr_bda7bb6a:


    nar "I cut through it and come to my door, but I don't go in."


translate English day10_cr_0909f463:


    nar "I stop not out of fear or concern, but because I hear Maya crying on the other side."


translate English day10_cr_c685ff99:


    nar "A voice that I've heard, but can't place, is comforting her in her quiet weeping."


translate English day10_cr_7092b845:


    nar "For some reason, it feels so natural to hear her crying right now. I start to feel like I'm dreaming while standing up."


translate English day10_cr_578832ea:


    my "I was wrong...{w} I've been wrong this whole time..."


translate English day10_cr_1443ec74:


    nar "Yeah. She's been wrong too."


translate English day10_cr_ba00b151:


    nar "But I'm anxious, Maya.{w} I still don't know what I'm wrong about."


translate English day10_cr_c18c4a59:



    nvl clear
    "\n I love Claire.{w} If she wants to stay as the heroine of her own story, I'll gladly be her partner in it.{w} I love watching her having those ridiculous dreams of hers."


translate English day10_cr_9510c186:


    et "She speaks her mind to me, and she's always a bright spot, lightening up wherever we are.{w} I thought we were standing in the same place, but I've only been standing in her shadow this whole time."


translate English day10_cr_96c8f964:



    nvl clear
    "\n Whenever I recall her cheery voice, or the light bends and curves of her wound-covered body, I break out in a cold sweat.{w} When I close my eyes, I can vividly see her scarlet tongue foaming in the darkness, and as I feel like even my biological sense of rejection has dulled, I grow terrified that this will forever be where I belong."


translate English day10_cr_cadafe05:


    "Claire still hasn't returned to the stairwell. My feet burn like a woman in menopause.{w} Where am I even trying to go? If I'd known this would happen, I should have gone straight back to the dorm.{w} I don't plan on working. I don't have an appetite. I don't feel like talking to anyone."


translate English day10_cr_ff990535:


    et "I should have gone back to my room and slept as much as I wanted."


translate English day10_cr_50d5d9e8:


    nar "It's been a while since coming to the gardens, and they're so strange that even my weary mind sees it."


translate English day10_cr_944a2736:


    nar "Watering cans and garden trowels are scattered about, and all the tall roses have been cut, now covering the ground."


translate English day10_cr_be7876c0:


    nar "Maya's only ever taken care of the drooping weeds here; I don't see any flowers.{w} I hear a pair of shears snip."


translate English day10_cr_e1a1c43a:


    nar "When I look up, I see Bishop Haku, a pair of garden shears in her hands, standing there staring at me."


translate English day10_cr_d98eeb74:


    hk "Good morning, Lord [na].{w} Are you loving others as God loves you?"


translate English day10_cr_da251f6c:


    pl "Good morning. It's, um...{w} It's kind of been a while, huh? Bishop."


translate English day10_cr_e59925e3:


    hk "That isn't what I believe you should be saying..."


translate English day10_cr_290667e4:


    hk "Time passes quickly at the temple. If you don't meet with many others and gain information, you'll be weeded out quickly."


translate English day10_cr_34de5961:


    pl "I haven't been feeling well lately... I'll start getting up early tomorrow."


translate English day10_cr_bd271256:


    hk "Are you sure...?{w} You aren't trying to fool me because my memory is spotty, are you?"


translate English day10_cr_4eff3d16:


    pl "Course not. I still got my work done today, even though I was late."


translate English day10_cr_a52b7fb2:


    pl "Hey... Why's this place such a mess?{w} Did you do this, Bishop?"


translate English day10_cr_f5241fec:


    hk "I'm not certain myself.{w} I heard that Sister Maya loved flowers, so I was having her take care of the garden..."


translate English day10_cr_65f55fa5:


    hk "From what it looks like, she hasn't been here for a few days.{w} I suppose you do get bored more quickly when you're younger..."


translate English day10_cr_f136ce17:


    pl "Bored?{w} I really doubt that. She loved doing this."


translate English day10_cr_7eae5c59:


    hk "I feel the same way, Brother."


translate English day10_cr_ca878277:


    nar "Bishop Haku smiles and takes a step to the side."


translate English day10_cr_71fcbb00:


    nar "A simple step brings her feet over to step on the cut rose blossoms."


translate English day10_cr_b7d9b22d:


    hk "Do you see this? Branches that didn't need to be cut have been cut."


translate English day10_cr_f6469018:


    hk "She never struck me as someone so lacking in knowledge and love that she would blindly harm the flowers like this..."


translate English day10_cr_278f1acd:


    hk "Has her emotional or mental state changed somehow?"


translate English day10_cr_59a19dbf:


    nar "Both her voice and her expression are as gentle and soft as ever, but the words have thorns."


translate English day10_cr_fae5367e:


    nar "Did she hear about what happened yesterday too?{w} How much does she know?"


translate English day10_cr_a30733ca:


    nar "Bishop Haku seems fairly certain I'm the one who affected Maya's emotional state."


translate English day10_cr_c75153ef:


    nar "So, instead of going to Maya, who caused this problem, she came to me."


translate English day10_cr_49fe50cc:


