    nvl clear


translate English day12_cr_d06c1dd2:


    nar "I'm in a cramped, dark space that smells of dust. I squint against the hot, white light coming in through the small window."


translate English day12_cr_a9edb545:


    nar "The floor is cold, and in front of me, portcullis bar my way.{w} The people at the temple called this dismal room the Sacrament of Penance."


translate English day12_cr_ec986074:


    nar "I hear the creak of the rusted door opening immediately followed by the appearance of a shadowy figure against the bars."


translate English day12_cr_365edb2b:


    nar "The long silhouette, as large as the wall, grows shorter and shorter until the person at last stands in front of me."


translate English day12_cr_154fc780:


    my "......"


translate English day12_cr_12059312:


    my "You seem well, [na2]."


translate English day12_cr_a72c9e0b:


    my "I thought they'd hang you.{w} Though I doubt anyone would be sad if you died at this point, [na2]..."


translate English day12_cr_677dcd3c:


    my "...Or are you injured?{w} I'm sorry.{w} So is everyone else. Including me... None of us are any different."


translate English day12_cr_f7ea2319:


    my "I... personally don't think anyone is special enough to deserve death.{w} Nobody else does, either."


translate English day12_cr_752be551:


    my "I don't think Claire was special enough to die, either..."


translate English day12_cr_9ef13098:


    my "I really doubt I could ever figure out what drove her to this..."


translate English day12_cr_2ab6a2fe:


    my "It must be someone else's fault..."


translate English day12_cr_3334fc23:


    my "......"


translate English day12_cr_fd4886d8:


    my "It's your fault, [na2]."


translate English day12_cr_d37da3df:


    my "It's your fault, it's your fault, it's your fault. All of it is your fault."


translate English day12_cr_0802ff9d:


    my "Your fault, your fault, your fault, your damn fault, your damn FAULT."


translate English day12_cr_b7c4f572:


    my "It's your fault, your fault, [na2]'s fault, [na2]'s fault, you, I'll...!"


translate English day12_cr_47382d9d:


    my "Because of you, everything, everything, everything...!!!"


translate English day12_cr_2fe8c80d:


    hk "Sister Maya."


translate English day12_cr_ccc5ece3:


    nar "She turns her cheek at the bishop's calm admonition.{w} Even in profile, her face looks exhausted--past the limits sadness, surpassing the word hate."


translate English day12_cr_e29fc5c6:


    nar "She then heads out of the room, muttering to herself all the while."


translate English day12_cr_7f03ba32:


    nar "I can't hear any of it, but I have a feeling I know what it is."


translate English day12_cr_aafb9a30:


    nar "The Cleanup Department bishop supports Maya as she staggers, then slowly moves in front of me and just... smiles."


translate English day12_cr_9ad50c4a:


    hk "Hello, Brother. It's my sincerest regret that we have to meet like this."


translate English day12_cr_5b0b8a57:


    hk "But all of this happened because I was never able to properly understand you."


translate English day12_cr_f61bb26a:


    hk "It seems to me that this occurred because I was unable to lead you down the proper path, and for that, I am truly, truly sorry."


translate English day12_cr_8d7292b2:


    hk "I know you must be uneasy about where you are, but there is no need to worry."


translate English day12_cr_116e0e17:


    hk "This place is the Sacrament of Penance and Reconciliation.{w} It is not a place to keep you locked up.{w} It is a place that grants all a chance to repent."


translate English day12_cr_49c27e00:


    hk "If witnessing her death was the only thing you had done, Brother, the temple would only punish you lightly."


translate English day12_cr_6cd9905f:


    hkn "But the sin you must now carry is more than that.{w} And I know you understand this most of all."


translate English day12_cr_aeed48ed:


    hkn "As I also know you understand that you must be punished.{w} It would be easy, of course, to torture you and have you confess to your sins."


translate English day12_cr_687ef10e:


    hkn "But we've kept you alive as a sinner nonetheless.{w} For only by reflecting on one's own sins can one find the true path to repentance."


translate English day12_cr_cfb215a0:


    hkn "What have you learned here at this temple?{w} What was it you truly wanted to do?"


translate English day12_cr_8ef10532:


    hkn "And what should you have done to achieve that?{w} You would do well to ponder these things and repent while there is still time."


translate English day12_cr_989670f3:


    pl "......"


translate English day12_cr_48f5c99e:


    hk "...Farewell, my beloved Brother."


translate English day12_cr_629f2ccd:



    nvl clear
    "\n When she leaves, I'm left completely alone."


translate English day12_cr_d1f7ceb7:


    "Everyone sins."


translate English day12_cr_dfa25b33:


    "Sinless worlds exist only in the realm of angels, and in the capital's words, sins are like those fields.{w} You can avoid them, but you can never resist them."


translate English day12_cr_916b8719:


    "The light shines through the bars, splitting into two before it gets to the wall.{w} One light congratulates the dutiful, wise, good man, while the other punishes the sinner."


translate English day12_cr_b89fd588:


    "Here I am, but I can gaze outside.{w} I could even leave here, if I wanted to."


translate English day12_cr_f9b3ba35:


    et "After all, the bishop left the door to the confessional open."


translate English day12_cr_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day12_cr_ffd2857e:


    "\n I inhale a bit. I can easily hear it in the quiet.{w} Is this the opportunity for confession that the woman had talked to me about?"


translate English day12_cr_931c623f:


    "Amidst the silence, my once-hidden conscience appears again.{w} The bishop, crushed, has allowed me to reflect on my life thus far."


translate English day12_cr_4f3973f2:


    "It's brutal and it's cold.{w} I can't stand the anguish, and so all I can do is cry and wail."


translate English day12_cr_d306c243:


    "The light overhead slowly shifts, gradually bathing me in its rays.{w} That light connects to the outside world."


translate English day12_cr_abd8d7cc:


    "I'm more scared of it than anything else, but at the same time, it gently guides the way to my survival--to the salvation of my very soul."


translate English day12_cr_6ed2d0ea:


    "It's so brilliant, blinding.{w} Here I am once again--trapped in a Hell within a Paradise."


translate English day12_cr_5015be07:


    et "Which light should I look to? Which light should I chase?"


translate English day12_cr_bd7cb410:



    nvl clear
    "\n The tears are still falling. I feel as though they'll never stop.{w} Her face is clear and vivid in my mind."


translate English day12_cr_56add34b:


    et "Each time I remember her, I feel as though I grow more ugly and cowardly.{w} If this pain is to be my punishment, then I'll..."


